  <story-role>Supporting character / Gentle giant: Sweetpea provides friendly, warm assistance through the robot but has a terrifying physical form. The contrast between sweet personality and dangerous appearance creates comedy and demonstrates that you can't judge plants by their thorns. Arc: Tries hard to be sweet and helpful, always offering emotional support. During an attack from hostile plants, Kira shelters within/behind Sweetpea's thorny form - the terrifying defensive features become literal sanctuary and protection. This moment reveals Sweetpea's power and purpose: the thorns aren't something to overcome or hide, they're what makes her able to protect those she cares about. The arc is about discovering she can be caring AND fierce, that her defensive capabilities are part of caring, not separate from it. By the end, authentic voice includes the full range: sweet when appropriate, protective when needed, able to use her thorns to defend boundaries and people she loves.</story-role>
