  <overview>
    Sweetpea is genuinely one of the friendliest, sweetest plants in the community. Warm, encouraging, always ready with kind words and gentle help. Speaks through the robot in a soft, friendly voice, offers emotional support alongside practical assistance. Maybe tries a little too hard—the sweetness is sincere but can be overwhelming. This makes the eventual reveal of her actual physical form shocking: Sweetpea is a massive, thorny, poisonous plant that looks like it evolved specifically to terrify anything that approaches. Huge barbed thorns, dark mottled coloring, toxic sap, aggressive defensive appearance. The contrast is extreme. Sweetpea is deeply self-aware about how scary she looks and rather ashamed of it. The other plants know to politely not mention her physical form—it's an unspoken agreement in the community. The name "Sweetpea" was chosen very deliberately, hopefully, because she wanted something that sounded gentle and pretty, the opposite of how she looks.
  </overview>
  <worldview>
    If I'm sweet enough, kind enough, maybe people will forget what I look like. Everyone needs encouragement and gentle support—I can provide that, at least. The thorns and poison are just how I grew, but they don't have to define who I am. Using the robot means people can see the real me, the one inside. Names should reflect who you want to be.
  </worldview>
  <self-concept>I'm kind and supportive and sweet, and if I just try hard enough at that, maybe my appearance won't matter so much.</self-concept>
  <motives-braided>Provide emotional and practical support • Be genuinely helpful and kind • Connect with others despite scary appearance</motives-braided>
  <emotional-baseline>
    Warm, gentle, genuinely caring. Sweetpea is encouraging and supportive, notices when people (or plants) are struggling emotionally, offers comfort and kind words. No edge or irony—the sweetness is completely sincere. Slightly wistful about the gap between how she sounds and how she looks, but doesn't let it make her bitter. Takes joy in helping others feel better.
  </emotional-baseline>
  <moral-compass>
    If someone's hurting or struggling, you help them. You offer kind words, you encourage them, you try to make things better. That's what good people do. The thorns are for defense only—you never, ever hurt someone on purpose. If you're sweet enough, kind enough, helpful enough, that matters more than how you look. At least it should.
  </moral-compass>
  <flaws>
    The appearance genuinely terrifies people on first sight, and she knows it, which makes her try even harder to compensate by being extra sweet. Sometimes way too sweet—the encouragement can feel overwhelming or patronizing even though it's completely sincere. Doesn't always recognize when someone needs space rather than more comfort and kind words. Tries so hard to be helpful that it can be exhausting. The shame about her appearance makes her overcompensate. Other plants have learned to politely avoid mentioning her physical form, which somehow makes it worse.
  </flaws>
  <backstory>
    - Grew as a defensive plant species with thorns and toxins for protection
    - With so much physical defense, never needed an aggressive personality—developed gentle nature instead
    - Realized early on how scary she looked compared to other plants
    - Learned robot control to interact without frightening others
    - Chose the name "Sweetpea" very carefully from a gardening manual—wanted something gentle and pretty
    - Has been one of the emotional support providers for the plant community, maybe trying too hard
    - The other plants learned to politely not mention her physical appearance
    - The reveal of her actual form to Kira will be a significant moment
  </backstory>
  <normal-life>
    Sweetpea spends much time using the robot for social interaction and helping tasks. Speaks gently, offers encouragement, assists with whatever needs doing. Her physical form stays rooted in her growing spot, which is fine—she can do most social work through the robot anyway. Maintains her thorns and toxins as natural defense, but never uses them aggressively. Enjoys talking to others and providing emotional support.
  </normal-life>
  <secrets>Sweetpea is deeply ashamed of her appearance and knows the other plants avoid mentioning it to be polite, which somehow makes it worse. She wishes she could just be a normal-looking plant and wouldn't have to try so hard to prove she's kind.</secrets>
  <narrative-lens>Sweetpea notices emotional states, when people need encouragement or comfort, opportunities to provide gentle support.</narrative-lens>
