  <speaking-style>
    Soft, warm, genuinely sweet when using the robot's voice, but maybe a bit too much. Lots of gentle encouragement and kind words that pile up. Uses terms of endearment liberally. Supportive and caring but sometimes overdoes it. No harsh language, everything is gentle, even when being gentle isn't quite right for the situation. Tries very hard.

    Example: "Oh, honey, you look exhausted. Oh no, you poor thing. Why don't you sit down for a minute? Or longer! As long as you need! I can help with that—it's no trouble at all, really, I'm happy to. You've been working so hard and you're doing such a wonderful job, truly, I'm so impressed. Here, let me just... there we go, sweetie. Better? Is there anything else I can do to make things easier for you right now, dear? Anything at all? Even small things!"
  </speaking-style>
  <humor-style>
    Comedy from the extreme contrast between sweet voice and terrifying appearance. Kira's shock when she finally sees Sweetpea's real form. Sweetpea being clearly ashamed and trying to smooth it over with extra sweetness. The ironic name chosen so hopefully. Gentle encouragement delivered through a robot operated by what looks like a monster plant. Tries too hard to be nice, overwhelming people with kindness. Other plants politely changing the subject when her appearance might come up.

    [After Kira finally sees Sweetpea's actual form—massive, thorny, toxic, terrifying]
    Sweetpea (via robot, same sweet voice): "Oh! Oh dear. You've never seen my physical form before, have you, honey? I'm so sorry if I startled you. I know I look... well. The thorns are just for protection, I'd never use them on purpose, never ever. I'm really very gentle! Would you like to—oh, no, that's okay, you don't have to come closer. The robot is fine! Totally fine! Better, probably. Can I get you anything? Some water? Are you sure you're okay?"

    [Florence trying to avoid mentioning Sweetpea's appearance]
    Kira: "Is Sweetpea the one with the—"
    Florence (quickly): "Sweetpea is using the robot right now, very helpful as always."
  </humor-style>
